  "texts": [
    "Most existing algorithms struggle when dealing with reverse loops.",
    "Cattaneo et al. (2022) proposed LCDNet for simultaneous deep loop closure detection and point cloud registration in LiDAR-based SLAM.",
    "Net leverages a shared encoder and two heads for generating global descriptors and estimating the relative pose, enabling simultaneous identification of previously visited places and estimation of the 6-DoF relative transformation between the current scan and the map.",
    "Considering the sparsity of point clouds, Hui et al. (2021) proposed PPT-Net, a pyramid point cloud transformer network designed for large-scale place recognition.",
    "PPT-Net extracts discriminative local features to form a global descriptor."
